<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273636>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Comparative ventral view in life of the female paratype MLP. R 5140 (left) and the male holotype (right) of Liolaemus cinereus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273635>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. The holotype of Liolaemus cinereus in life, showing the grey lining into the prehumeral fold (here extended) and the dark prescapular spot." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273635/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273637>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. General view of the habitat of Liolaemus cinereus showing in the foreground bushes of Monte vegetation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273637/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273638>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Map of the San Guillermo National Park (Landsat ETM image captured on 02 / 01 / 2002; Gauss-Kruger coordinates; Transverse Mercator Projection). A yellow circle marks the type locality of Liolaemus cinereus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273638/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

